snippet.textDisplay: VR headsets are not nearly as complex and hassle filled as you make it seem. Saying the tech isn't ready for consumers is just an opinion I really don't agree with. I still remember my mind being blown when I first put on my Oculus Rift S, which requires no set up at all, just 1 single wire going to my PC and that's it. I picked up the headset on black Friday this year because they had it on sale for $350. Some of the best money I've ever spent as far as gaming purchases go. I waited years to hop into VR and honestly I was only buying this headset because I knew I would need one to play Half Life Alyx and the Oculus was on sale so I said F it and picked it up. I have been playing VR almost everyday. Playing Boneworks VR was one of the single coolest experiences I've ever had in gaming.
